race.comment: AITU (4) took on a much tougher race at Flemington when last seen and wasn't disgraced, fading late to finish ninth, beaten five lengths. The maiden win prior was good and coming back to 1600m in a Class 1 looks a lovely set up. ISLAND BOY (5) also tackled the Flemington race, beaten eight lengths into 12th there. He too won his maiden well prior and can bounce back. CASH CONVERTER (2) is knocking on the door, finding it tough to break through for that elusive second win. He found the line well for second at Warrnambool, giving the indication 1600m would now suit nicely. ON BROADWAY (6) has just found one better at both runs this time in but should be ready to peak now up on speed with Zahra booked. MISS CASTELVECCHIO (8) was poor last time when in the market, look for improvement.
